cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.PL, cs.MS, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely sub-category as the paper deals with modal versions of resource-conscious logics and presents an axiomatisation and a sequent calculus for the language of propositional intuitionistic linear logic. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper mentions investigating agency in multi-agent systems. 
3. cs.PL (Programming Languages) is another possible sub-category as the paper deals with extensions of linear logic. 
4. cs.MS (Mathematical Software) is a possible sub-category as the paper presents a formal proof theory. 
5. cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a less likely sub-category, but still possible as the paper deals with resource models and their interpretation.
